{"TopicId":210295,"ForumId":112,"TopicTitle":"KSP 2 science system","CreatedByName":"Rutabaga22","CreatedById":221143,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-26T18:30:50Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Rutabaga22","CreatedById":221143,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-26T18:30:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve seen discussions of this popping up and wanted to hear some ideas about it.\u003Cbr\u003E\nHere\u0027s how I think it should work.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI think KSP2 science should use logical progression based on experiments, so your thermometer experiment doesn\u0027t give you better ladders. I think there should bet wo types of data. Material data and Atmospheric Data.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaterial data should be able to be mainly required for things like command pods, radiators, wheels, fuel tanks, and ladders. Material data would be gained from mystery goo, science junior, scanning arm, etc.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nAtmospheric data should be required\u00A0 for heat shields, parachutes, plane stuff, decouplers, and fairings. Atmospheric data would be collected from thermometers, barometers, atmospheric science experiment from Ksp that I don\u0027t remember the name of, etc.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-26T19:26:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224191194\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022210295\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221666809050\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022221143\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rutabaga22\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n55 minutes ago, Rutabaga22 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso your thermometer experiment doesn\u0027t give you better ladders.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey can measure gravity with thermometer as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.eetimes.com/measuring-a-buildings-height-with-a-barometer/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.eetimes.com/measuring-a-buildings-height-with-a-barometer/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, thermometer \u002B watch or rope = gravity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ryaja","CreatedById":221431,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-26T23:12:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224191238\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022210295\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221666812418\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey can measure gravity with thermometer as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.eetimes.com/measuring-a-buildings-height-with-a-barometer/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.eetimes.com/measuring-a-buildings-height-with-a-barometer/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, thermometer \u002B watch or rope = gravity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat says\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Ebarometer\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0not\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Ethermometer\u00A0\u003C/em\u003Eand\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eheight\u00A0\u003C/em\u003Enot\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eweight\u00A0\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludeq